{code:java}
public void setZoneName(final String name) {
  Preconditions.checkNotNull(name == null)-------error parameter for checkNotNull
  zoneName = name;
}
{code}
Like above, in 3.x, the checkNotNull function gets wrong parameter in two cases: \{{ZoneReencryptionStatus#setZoneName}} and \{{AdminHelper#HelpCommand#HelpCommand}}

In 2.x, the error occurs once in \{{AdminHelper#HelpCommand#HelpCommand}}

